How to use templates:

__________________ general notes __________________
Variables named "TODO_x" must be specified for calculation to run. 
Variables names "x_opt" can be excluded if desired. 
------------------ ccsd_template ------------------
Structure Variables:
charge                              - TODO_CHARGE
multiplicity                        - TODO_MULT
coordinates (in xyz or zmol format) - TODO_MOL


Calculation Variables:
Basis                           - TODO_BASIS 
Memory                          - mem_opt
Type of Hartree-Fock            - hf_opt
Hartree-Fock algorithm          - scf_opt
Maximum number of HF iterations - scf_cycle_opt
Integral Threshold              - thresh_opt
HF convergence threshold        - conv_opt
CC convergence threshold        - cc_conv_opt


Recommendations:
As discussed, start with STO-3G for the basis for test of project validity. 
Memory - can likely run STO-3G without needing to specify. If you run into issues, set a number s.t. 1000 = 1GB. For the largest jobs I've run I have used 300000. If you hit that point, I would also specify the variable "MEM_STATIC 5000".
Type of Hartree-Fock - since we're running transition states, should set this to TRUE. However, for "easy" systems should set to FALSE which saves half the memory. 
The Hartree-Fock algorithm - start with DIIS-GDM, if issues persist run GDM. 
Thresh - integral threshold for neglecting, 15 should be more than adequate. 
scf convergence - 10 should be good for these cases. Lower if calculations almost converge but don't quite hit the threshold. Or, you could increase the number of iterations in the number of iterations.
scf iterations - see above. 
CC_convergence - 7 should be good.


_________________ mp2_template __________________ 

Same structure variables and calculation variables. Should be good to use same parameters.



